<span id="freeTextContainer15148146307578087614">Dr. DuBois is nothing short of genius. His in-depth analysis of the condition of people of African descent here in America is brilliant. The Souls of Black Folk is not one to be read and then shoved in a corner but should be reread time and again. I certainly will. Published in 1903 but is still just as relevant and important today.</span>

